Wave 13.5 real-HW data showed bigger sample_frames is SLOWER, not faster
— per-chunk cost scales superlinearly (likely P54C 8 KB L1 D-cache vs
chunk memcpy ≥ 8 KB at 2048-frame chunks). Drop the 1024-frame override
and let SDL3 pick its 512-frame default (2048 B chunks).

Pairs with patches/SDL/0022 which deepens the SB16 ring from 4 chunks
(92 ms buffer) to 16 chunks (372 ms buffer) so we get audio glitch
protection without paying the cache-pressure tax.

Predicted: title scene 11.6 fps (vs 10.5 wave 13.4 / 10.2 wave 13.5),
cleaner audio in transitions. cmod-heavy menus still ~2 fps — that's
per-pixel cmod cost, addressable by Lever 3 (8bpp + palette) only.

Init log adjusted to show "(default — SDL3 picks 512 at 22050 Hz)"
when no env override is set, vs the prior "1024" for the wave 13.5
default.
---
 src/sound/SoundManager.cpp | 37 ++++++++++++++++---------------------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 21 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
index d2d909e..d5fb824 100644
--- a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
+++ b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
@@ -34,28 +34,23 @@ bool SoundManager::init()
 {
   LOG_INFO("Sound system init");
 
-  // DOS-PORT (patch 0066, Phase 9 wave 13.5): increase the SDL3 audio
-  // chunk size from the default 512 frames to 1024 frames at our 22050 Hz
-  // sample rate. The audio thread does fixed-overhead work per chunk
-  // (mutex lock + AudioStream pull + ConvertAudio + push to ring),
-  // measured at ~6-7 ms per chunk on PODP 5V83. Default chunk = 23 ms of
-  // audio at 22050 stereo S16; with the 4-chunk ring buffer that's a
-  // 92 ms total buffer, and at our wave 13.4 ~10 fps cadence the audio
-  // thread refills the entire ring (~4 chunks) per per-flip yield,
-  // costing ~27 ms / flip. Doubling chunk size halves the per-yield
-  // refill count to ~2 chunks → predicted ~13 ms / flip yield cost.
-  // Trade-off: SFX latency grows from 92 ms → 184 ms (still fine for
-  // Cave Story's gameplay feel). Tunable via env var:
-  //   SET SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES=2048   (more aggressive)
-  //   SET SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES=512    (revert to SDL3 default)
-  // SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE priority lets the env var win over our default.
-  if (!SDL_GetHint(SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES))
-  {
-    SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES, "1024",
-                            SDL_HINT_NORMAL);
-  }
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0066, Phase 9 wave 13.5/13.6): keep SDL3's default
+  // sample_frames=512 (=2048 B chunks, =23 ms audio per chunk).
+  // Wave 13.5 experiment (real-HW PODP 5V83) tested 512 vs 1024 vs 2048:
+  // 512 was fastest (86 ms/flip steady title), 1024 and 2048 were ~99 ms.
+  // Per-chunk cost scales with chunk size — likely L1 cache pressure
+  // (P54C 8 KB D-cache vs 8 KB chunk memcpy at 2048 frames thrashes the
+  // cache for subsequent game-thread work). The audio buffer underrun
+  // risk that motivated chunk increase is fixed instead by bumping
+  // RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS in the SDL-side patch (vendor/SDL/src/audio/dos/
+  // SDL_dosaudio_sb.c) so we get 372 ms of buffer at 512-frame chunks.
+  // Tunable via env var if needed:
+  //   SET SDL_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES=1024  (probably slower)
+  //   SET SDL_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES=2048  (probably much slower)
   LOG_INFO("Sound system: SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES={}",
-           SDL_GetHint(SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES));
+           SDL_GetHint(SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES) ?
+             SDL_GetHint(SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES) :
+             "(default — SDL3 picks 512 at 22050 Hz)");
 
   // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer registers decoders at compile time (we built it
   // with SDLMIXER_VORBIS_STB=ON for stb_vorbis OGG, SDLMIXER_WAVE=ON for
